# Vulnerabilities in the base python:3.11-slim image's pre-installed
# setuptools and pip — vendored deps under /usr/local/lib/.../setuptools/_vendor.
# These tools are not used at runtime: our application code runs out of a
# separate venv at /opt/venv that has up-to-date setuptools and wheel.
# Tracked: bump base image when python:3.11-slim ships fresher tooling.
CVE-2026-23949   # jaraco.context 5.3.0 — vendored in base setuptools
CVE-2026-24049   # wheel 0.45.1 — vendored in base setuptools

# starlette HIGH CVE — pinned transitively by fastapi 0.115.x. Fix is in
# starlette 0.49.1, which needs a fastapi major version bump (0.118+).
# Deferred: low-impact DoS via Range header on a service that is not
# exposed to untrusted external traffic.
CVE-2025-62727
